    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const candidates = $input.first().json.candidates;\n\nconst sorted = candidates.sort((a, b) => b.max_score - a.max_score);\n\nreturn sorted.map(candidate => ({ json: candidate }));"
      },
      "id": "32eac7b8-45b5-4fc6-a323-6d3d697e88bf",
      "name": "Sort by Max Score",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        2448,
        656
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert resume parser.\n\nAnalyze the following resume and extract structured information.\n\nResume:\n\n{{ $json.text }}\n\nRules:\n\n- Return ONLY valid JSON.\n- Do not include markdown.\n- Do not include explanations.\n- Do not infer information that is not explicitly present in the resume.\n- Extract languages separately from skills.\n- Do NOT include languages inside the skills array.\n- Estimate years_experience based on the candidate's work history.\n- Extract only relevant professional, technical, ERP, consulting, management, business, and software skills explicitly mentioned.\n\nEnglish Level Rules:\n- Native\n- Fluent\n- Professional\n- Advanced\n- Intermediate\n- Basic\n- Mentioned\n- Not Specified\n\nIf English appears in the Languages section, classify it using the closest available level.\n\nReturn this exact schema:\n\n{\n  \"candidate_name\": \"\",\n  \"years_experience\": 0,\n  \"english_level\": \"\",\n  \"other_languages\": [],\n  \"skills\": [],\n  \"education\": \"\",\n  \"previous_roles\": []\n}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a resume parsing expert. Extract structured data accurately from resumes. Focus on quantifiable experience, technical skills, and relevant qualifications."
        }
      },
      "id": "1dd0cb31-2317-47e6-ab1f-a475afe42d17",
      "name": "Parse Resume Data",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        2032,
        256
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
